clipy (0.2.4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: auto-paste on select was unreliable — the entry reached the clipboard but the
    synthesised Ctrl+V usually did nothing, so you had to press Ctrl+V yourself. Root cause
    was a focus-return race: the cursor menu steals keyboard focus while open, and the old
    code closed the menu asynchronously while pasting on an independent 140ms timer, so the
    keystroke fired before the compositor handed focus back to your app (and thus went
    nowhere on native Wayland). Selecting an entry now runs a deterministic sequence —
    close the menu, restore focus to the previously-focused window (clipy/x11.py
    get/set_input_focus), then inject Ctrl+V once after a short settle (paste_now()).
    Verified through the real cursor-menu code path pasting into a native Wayland app:
    10/10 successful selections (was intermittent before).

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 17:30:00 +0000

clipy (0.2.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * The history/snippets hotkey now opens a NATIVE MENU AT THE CURSOR, matching Clipy's
    macOS menu exactly: numbered history entries (folders of ten — "0 - 9", "10 - 19" —
    once there are more than ten), snippet folders as submenus, then Clear History / Edit
    Snippets / Preferences / Quit. This replaces the search-box popup window, which did not
    resemble Clipy's actual UI. Built with GtkPopoverMenu anchored to a 1x1 override-redirect
    host placed at the pointer via libX11.
  * Verified end-to-end: selecting an entry sets the clipboard and pastes it into the
    focused native-Wayland app through the RemoteDesktop portal (Ctrl+V), with the portal
    session restored silently from the saved token on startup.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Sun, 05 Jul 2026 16:45:00 +0000

clipy (0.2.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Auto-paste now reaches native Wayland apps. XTEST only delivers synthetic input to
    XWayland/X11 windows, so pasting into Wayland-native apps did nothing. Added a
    RemoteDesktop-portal injector (clipy/inject.py): one persistent portal session set up
    at startup (GNOME prompts once; a saved restore-token keeps it silent afterwards),
    injecting Ctrl+V via NotifyKeyboardKeycode. XTEST kept as an X11/XWayland fallback.
    Verified end-to-end: paste lands in a native Wayland window driven by the daemon.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 14:00:00 +0000

clipy (0.2.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Auto-paste on select now actually pastes. Selecting a history/snippet entry
    sets the clipboard and synthesises Ctrl+V into the previously focused window via
    XTEST (libX11/libXtst through ctypes — zero installs, works under XWayland and,
    on Mutter, native Wayland windows). Deferred ~140ms so focus returns to the
    target app first. Falls back to ydotool if present. Toggle in General prefs.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

clipy (0.2.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Feature parity pass toward the macOS Clipy:
    - History/snippets now open as a COMPACT POPUP AT THE MOUSE CURSOR (via libX11
      ctypes under XWayland), replacing the centered window.
    - Default hotkeys changed to Clipy's combos: History Ctrl+Shift+V,
      Snippets Ctrl+Shift+B, Menu Ctrl+Shift+C.
    - Type filters: choose which clipboard categories to store
      (plain text / rich text / files / images) + new Type preferences tab.
    - Menu options: image thumbnails in the menu, start-numbering-from-zero,
      show/hide type icons, show/hide Clear History, reorder-after-paste.
    - Confirm-before-clear-history and confirm-before-delete-snippet.
    - Exclude-apps by window class (best-effort; X11/XWayland apps only on GNOME
      Wayland) + new Applications preferences tab.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Sat, 04 Jul 2026 10:00:00 +0000

clipy (0.1.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: tray menu did not open on click. The dbusmenu GetLayout serialized each
    child menu item double-wrapped in an extra variant. Python's .unpack() tolerated
    it, but the GNOME AppIndicator extension uses GJS deep_unpack(), which threw
    "TypeError: (destructured parameter) is not iterable" and rendered no menu.
    Children are now emitted as plain (ia{sv}av) variants, matching real indicators.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 13:00:00 +0000

clipy (0.1.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: tray icon did not appear. The StatusNotifierItem was registered by bus
    name, which makes hosts look for the item at /StatusNotifierItem; ours lives
    at a custom path. Now registered by object path (busname@path form), matching
    what the GNOME AppIndicator extension expects. Registration errors are now
    logged instead of silently ignored.

 -- Bhavesh Prasad <prasadbhavesh7@gmail.com>  Fri, 03 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

clipy (0.1.0) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial release: Linux clone of the macOS Clipy clipboard manager.
    Clipboard history (text + images), snippets with folders, tray icon
    (StatusNotifierItem + dbusmenu), global hotkeys via GNOME custom shortcuts,
    searchable pop-ups, preferences, and launch-at-login. GTK4 / PyGObject.

